00:23:34,179 --> 00:23:36,248
-It's so good.
-Very good.

511
00:23:36,715 --> 00:23:38,583
They're two different dishes.

512
00:23:38,650 --> 00:23:40,752
-Yes, that's why--
-Two dishes in one go.

513
00:23:40,819 --> 00:23:41,887
-Yes.
-For real.

514
00:23:41,953 --> 00:23:44,623
Why do you recommend eating the egg first?

515
00:23:44,689 --> 00:23:46,324
You'll be intaking fiber.

516
00:23:46,391 --> 00:23:49,294
So it's to line your stomach beforehand.

517
00:23:49,361 --> 00:23:52,264
-Like an egg on naengmyeon?
-Yes, correct.

518
00:23:52,330 --> 00:23:54,232
You're considerate of your customers.

519
00:23:54,299 --> 00:23:55,133
That's right.

520
00:23:55,200 --> 00:23:56,802
It tastes better warm.

521
00:23:56,868 --> 00:23:57,936
It's very savory.

522
00:23:58,003 --> 00:23:58,870
It's so good.

523
00:23:58,937 --> 00:24:01,773
This is a nutritious breakfast.
Very nutritious.

524
00:24:01,840 --> 00:24:04,075
My stomach feels protected.

525
00:24:04,142 --> 00:24:06,745
I should've had more to drink
if I knew I'd come here.

526
00:24:07,979 --> 00:24:09,247
This is warmed up?

527
00:24:09,314 --> 00:24:10,182
Yes.

528
00:24:12,217 --> 00:24:16,555
THE TORYEOM PROCESS
TO WARM THE RICE

529
00:24:23,628 --> 00:24:24,996
It's so tasty.

530
00:24:25,530 --> 00:24:26,765
The normal is perfect.

531
00:24:26,832 --> 00:24:27,833
It's just right.

532
00:24:27,899 --> 00:24:29,000
-Just right.
-Certainly.

533
00:24:29,067 --> 00:24:30,869
This is spicy enough.

534
00:24:30,936 --> 00:24:33,171
This doesn't need pickled shrimp sauce.

535
00:24:33,638 --> 00:24:35,507
It's seasoned well.

536
00:24:37,609 --> 00:24:39,177
-Wow, it's good.
-So good.

537
00:24:39,244 --> 00:24:40,078
Spicy enough.

538
00:24:40,145 --> 00:24:42,514
What's this sourness?

539
00:24:42,581 --> 00:24:44,649
We added some kimchi.

540
00:24:44,716 --> 00:24:46,952
Why is there cuttlefish?

541
00:24:47,018 --> 00:24:48,653
For protein.

542
00:24:48,720 --> 00:24:51,189
These bean sprouts seem smaller.

543
00:24:51,256 --> 00:24:52,557
Our local bean sprouts.

544
00:24:52,624 --> 00:24:54,326
Jeonju is famous for these?

545
00:24:54,392 --> 00:24:56,628
Water here is rich in iron.

546
00:24:56,695 --> 00:24:59,631
JEONJU'S TASTY BEAN SPROUT
DUE TO QUALITY WATER

547
00:24:59,698 --> 00:25:02,534
What I hear is that people
ate a lot of bean sprouts

548
00:25:02,601 --> 00:25:04,903
because of the water here.

549
00:25:04,970 --> 00:25:06,671
JEONJU BEAN SPROUT
STANDARD OF SAFETY

550
00:25:09,875 --> 00:25:11,643
People want good bean sprouts.

551
00:25:11,710 --> 00:25:14,946
So the increasing demand
enables its further development.

552
00:25:15,013 --> 00:25:16,882
This isn't gourmet food.

553
00:25:16,948 --> 00:25:20,552
You can enjoy it easily
because It's easily accessible.

554
00:25:22,354 --> 00:25:26,525
-Merchants at markets need quick fixes.
-That's right.

555
00:25:26,591 --> 00:25:28,927
This is Korea's fast food.

556
00:25:28,994 --> 00:25:31,029
-Oh, yeah.
-Korean fast food.

557
00:25:31,096 --> 00:25:31,930
It really is.

558
00:25:31,997 --> 00:25:34,366
It comes out as quickly as fast food.

559
00:25:34,432 --> 00:25:35,567
Sit, and you're served.

560
00:25:40,906 --> 00:25:43,975
I reckon gukbap was
the number one fast food of Joseon.

561
00:25:46,878 --> 00:25:50,015
Out of all global fast foods with soup,

562
00:25:50,081 --> 00:25:52,851
I believe this is the fastest to cook

563
00:25:52,918 --> 00:25:55,220
and the tastiest.

564
00:25:55,287 --> 00:25:56,321
They need to eat fast

565
00:25:56,388 --> 00:25:58,089
to go back to work quickly.

566
00:25:58,156 --> 00:25:59,724
By mixing rice into soup,

567
00:25:59,791 --> 00:26:03,528
they just drink out of the bowl
and quickly get back to work.

568
00:26:04,195 --> 00:26:08,099
It saves time,
and it's tasty and energizing.

569
00:26:08,166 --> 00:26:10,302
That's what gukbap is about.

570
00:26:19,077 --> 00:26:21,479
TRADITIONAL MARKET TOURS
ARE ALWAYS FUN

571
00:26:23,515 --> 00:26:26,518
SSANGHWA TEA, A JEONJU SPECIALTY

572
00:26:27,352 --> 00:26:28,954
SSANGHWA TEA
A HEALTHY TEA WITH MEDICINAL HERBS

573
00:26:29,020 --> 00:26:30,388
Want to mix in rice?

574
00:26:31,122 --> 00:26:32,524
We mix rice into any liquid.

575
00:26:33,825 --> 00:26:35,827
THIS IS IT

576
00:26:35,894 --> 00:26:36,928
Where to now?

577
00:26:36,995 --> 00:26:38,096
-This time…
-Yes.

578
00:26:38,163 --> 00:26:39,764
-…blood sundae.
-Blood sundae?

579
00:26:39,831 --> 00:26:42,634
We usually put glass noodles
in blood sundaes.

580
00:26:42,701 --> 00:26:43,802
Right, glass noodles.

581
00:26:43,868 --> 00:26:47,038
This place adds a lot of pig blood

582
00:26:47,105 --> 00:26:48,707
so it's this reddish color.

583
00:26:48,773 --> 00:26:50,041
Oh, wow.

584
00:26:50,108 --> 00:26:51,509
A red-blood sundae.

585
00:26:51,576 --> 00:26:52,544
Hello.

586
00:26:52,611 --> 00:26:53,612
-Hello.
-Hello.

587
00:26:53,678 --> 00:26:55,580
BLOOD SUNDAE GUKBAP

588
00:26:55,647 --> 00:26:57,182
What are we eating?

589
00:26:57,248 --> 00:26:59,250
Special, normal, or the head?

590
00:27:01,152 --> 00:27:02,320
I want the special.

591
00:27:02,387 --> 00:27:03,622
Special for men.

592
00:27:03,688 --> 00:27:04,990
Again with the "men" thing.

593
00:27:05,056 --> 00:27:07,359
-I want the normal.
-Special for men.

594
00:27:07,425 --> 00:27:08,326
-Normal.
-Okay.

595
00:27:08,393 --> 00:27:09,794
-Me, too.
-Normal blood sundae.

596
00:27:09,861 --> 00:27:12,430
-One large blood sundae.
-No, let's eat small.

597
00:27:12,497 --> 00:27:14,165
-No, large is better.
-Large?

598
00:27:14,633 --> 00:27:15,567
Madam, we'd like…

599
00:27:15,634 --> 00:27:17,569
Don't shout, she's right there.

600
00:27:17,636 --> 00:27:19,537
Apologies for shouting.

601
00:27:20,005 --> 00:27:21,439
I thought you were outside.

602
00:27:21,506 --> 00:27:23,642
These are baby chives.

603
00:27:23,708 --> 00:27:26,011
One special and two normal.

604
00:27:26,077 --> 00:27:28,279
And one large blood sundae, please.

605
00:27:28,346 --> 00:27:30,649
You find blood sundaes in Seoul
at bunsik houses

606
00:27:30,715 --> 00:27:32,851
stuffed with glass noodles.

607
00:27:33,518 --> 00:27:35,820
I thought those were blood sundaes.

608
00:27:35,887 --> 00:27:37,055
There are various kinds.

609
00:27:37,122 --> 00:27:39,124
The North Korean-style blood sundaes.

610
00:27:39,190 --> 00:27:41,226
NORTH KOREAN-STYLE SUNDAE, PORK DAECHANG
FILLED WITH GLUTINOUS RICE AND SEONJI

611
00:27:43,595 --> 00:27:44,696
Jeju blood sundaes.

612
00:27:44,763 --> 00:27:47,065
TRADITIONAL JEJU SUNDAE
FILLED WITH BUCKWHEAT AND SEONJI

613
00:27:47,132 --> 00:27:49,234
-There they are.
-This is it.

614
00:27:49,300 --> 00:27:50,335
These look good.

615
00:27:50,802 --> 00:27:53,471
That is an exquisite color.

616
00:27:53,538 --> 00:27:55,106
These are made from makchang.

617
00:27:58,476 --> 00:28:00,011
Why is it called a blood sundae?

618
00:28:00,078 --> 00:28:01,980
It's made with blood.

619
00:28:05,383 --> 00:28:07,619
This originally included
only blood and green onions.

620
00:28:07,686 --> 00:28:09,320
KIM SUN-JA
RUNS A SUNDAE HOUSE OF 38 YEARS

621
00:28:09,387 --> 00:28:10,455
Methods have changed.

622
00:28:10,522 --> 00:28:12,257
We tried many ingredients,

623
00:28:12,323 --> 00:28:15,393
and we went through many failures

624
00:28:15,460 --> 00:28:17,529
so certain ratios have been created.

625
00:28:17,595 --> 00:28:19,931
A lot of blood goes in,
a two to three ratio.

626
00:28:19,998 --> 00:28:22,934
Two for blood and three for sauce.

627
00:28:23,001 --> 00:28:26,504
We also add the end of makchang
and some daechang too.

628
00:28:26,571 --> 00:28:28,440
That's our usual recipe.

629
00:28:28,506 --> 00:28:30,141
We stuff everything ourselves.

630
00:28:30,575 --> 00:28:31,476
Then we boil.

631
00:28:31,976 --> 00:28:34,746
This process is necessary
to create these sundaes.

632
00:28:35,747 --> 00:28:40,385
BLOOD SUNDAE TAKES 11 HOURS TO MAKE

633
00:28:41,419 --> 00:28:43,021
This is my first blood sundae.

634
00:28:43,088 --> 00:28:44,656
It differs regionally.

635
00:28:47,592 --> 00:28:48,927
Does this taste different?

636
00:28:48,993 --> 00:28:51,196
There isn't much makchang.

637
00:28:51,262 --> 00:28:52,097
Only this much.

638
00:28:52,163 --> 00:28:54,432
The rest is the thinner ones.

639
00:28:54,499 --> 00:28:55,700
Thinner ones, yes.

640
00:28:55,767 --> 00:28:57,402
Sir, take the tastiest bit.

641
00:28:57,469 --> 00:28:59,471
-There's more, you eat.
-The makchang.

642
00:28:59,938 --> 00:29:01,840
Let me add some pickled shrimp.

643
00:29:06,044 --> 00:29:07,078
I love this.

644
00:29:07,645 --> 00:29:08,780
Do you like it?

645
00:29:08,847 --> 00:29:11,216
I think I enjoy the smell of pork fat.

646
00:29:11,282 --> 00:29:13,084
The pork fat smell is strong.

647
00:29:13,551 --> 00:29:15,754
I don't know if I'm fond of it or not.

648
00:29:15,820 --> 00:29:17,655
It's okay, it doesn't smell.

649
00:29:17,722 --> 00:29:21,226
Usually, we put sesame seeds
into chili pepper paste.

650
00:29:21,292 --> 00:29:23,461
Mix, dip, then wrap it in sesame leaf.

651
00:29:23,528 --> 00:29:27,265
Then add some chives
and some garlic if you like garlic.

652
00:29:27,332 --> 00:29:29,634
-Okay, let me try this.
-See if you like it.

653
00:29:29,701 --> 00:29:30,769
-All right.
-Sure.

654
00:29:34,272 --> 00:29:37,275
The lettuce wrap
blends everything together.

655
00:29:37,342 --> 00:29:38,843
Right, the sesame leaf.

656
00:29:38,910 --> 00:29:40,545
This makes it much tastier.

657
00:29:40,612 --> 00:29:42,080
This alone is good too.

658
00:29:42,847 --> 00:29:47,352
HOW TO MAKE SUNDAE GUKBAP BROTH

659
00:29:48,019 --> 00:29:50,855
I've made sundae gukbap for 37, 38 years.

660
00:29:50,922 --> 00:29:54,292
When making gukbap,
broth is my first priority.

661
00:29:54,359 --> 00:29:56,995
A thick and tasty broth

662
00:29:57,061 --> 00:29:58,429
makes a tasty gukbap.

663
00:29:58,496 --> 00:30:00,799
This is pork bone.

664
00:30:00,865 --> 00:30:03,768
Not just any pork bone but the legs.

665
00:30:03,835 --> 00:30:07,205
I boil only the knee bones

666
00:30:07,272 --> 00:30:08,940
for a total of eight hours.

667
00:30:09,007 --> 00:30:10,375
Same with the intestines.

668
00:30:10,441 --> 00:30:12,243
I boil everything,

669
00:30:12,310 --> 00:30:14,012
rub it with my hands,

670
00:30:14,078 --> 00:30:16,014
wash and soak it in water

671
00:30:16,447 --> 00:30:18,183
to cool it down,

672
00:30:18,249 --> 00:30:19,984
and separate everything.

673
00:30:20,051 --> 00:30:21,319
Even with the slicing,

674
00:30:21,386 --> 00:30:23,555
it can't be too small or too big.

675
00:30:23,621 --> 00:30:25,824
Everything must be done just right.

676
00:30:27,425 --> 00:30:32,430
A WARM BOWL OF BROTH
THAT MELTS THE HEART

677
00:30:34,265 --> 00:30:36,301
You should add more chives.

678
00:30:36,367 --> 00:30:37,468
-Should I?
-Yes.

679
00:30:37,535 --> 00:30:39,003
I like its subtle taste.

680
00:30:39,070 --> 00:30:41,172
I guess that's why
there's little seasoning.

681
00:30:41,239 --> 00:30:43,908
It's stuffed to the brim
and I didn't even add rice.

682
00:30:43,975 --> 00:30:47,512
The bowl is filled with meat.
Wow, unbelievable.

683
00:30:48,079 --> 00:30:49,414
You put all the rice in?

684
00:30:49,480 --> 00:30:50,381
Yeah.

685
00:30:50,949 --> 00:30:52,150
Do you like to mix rice?

686
00:30:52,217 --> 00:30:53,952
Right, you said you don't.

687
00:30:54,419 --> 00:30:56,921
-Because you're nobility.
-Nobles don't mix rice.

688
00:30:58,089 --> 00:30:59,724
I don't even run in the rain.

689
00:31:00,191 --> 00:31:01,192
Really?

690
00:31:03,494 --> 00:31:05,663
We weren't even allowed
to lift our soup bowl.

691
00:31:05,730 --> 00:31:07,866
We couldn't speak during meals.

692
00:31:17,809 --> 00:31:19,344
It tastes so clean.

693
00:31:19,410 --> 00:31:21,012
If you add rice,

694
00:31:21,512 --> 00:31:24,649
the starch makes it thicker.

695
00:31:24,716 --> 00:31:26,885
You don't like it starchy?

696
00:31:26,951 --> 00:31:29,554
I prefer it thicker
when the rice starts blending in.

697
00:31:29,621 --> 00:31:30,889
THE SAVORY QUALITY
OF RICE IN THE BROTH

698
00:31:30,955 --> 00:31:32,824
Since you ask, I think I like it.

699
00:31:33,291 --> 00:31:34,692
Really?

700
00:31:35,193 --> 00:31:39,497
I think I prefer gukbap over
eating soup and rice separately.

701
00:31:39,564 --> 00:31:41,032
Isn't there a separate gukbap?

702
00:31:41,966 --> 00:31:45,470
But that's like saying,
"warm iced Americano."

703
00:31:45,536 --> 00:31:47,805
It can't exist.
How can gukbap be separate?

704
00:31:47,872 --> 00:31:50,074
The gukbap in Daegu seemed tasty.

705
00:31:50,141 --> 00:31:51,809
But I needed to keep my dignity.

706
00:31:51,876 --> 00:31:53,444
So I ate them together but separately.

707
00:31:56,314 --> 00:31:58,149
Out of all kinds of gukbap

708
00:31:58,816 --> 00:32:00,418
which do you enjoy eating most?

709
00:32:00,485 --> 00:32:01,920
I like bean sprout gukbap.

710
00:32:01,986 --> 00:32:03,187
Yukgaejang.

711
00:32:03,254 --> 00:32:04,522
-Yukgaejang.
-Yukgaejang.

712
00:32:05,123 --> 00:32:06,224
For me, sundae gukbap.

713
00:32:07,859 --> 00:32:10,495
Just across from
broadcasting stations at Yeouido,

714
00:32:10,561 --> 00:32:12,597
there was this place
called Hwamok Sundaeguk.

715
00:32:12,664 --> 00:32:14,332
It was a really old place.

716
00:32:14,399 --> 00:32:17,135
So having sundaeguk
from my early 20s,

717
00:32:17,201 --> 00:32:18,202
I became addicted.

718
00:32:18,269 --> 00:32:20,438
So when I think gukbap,
I think sundae gukbap.

719
00:32:20,905 --> 00:32:22,607
My actor friends took me there.

720
00:32:22,674 --> 00:32:25,343
I don't think anybody hates sundae gukbap.

721
00:32:25,410 --> 00:32:27,211
-I agree.
-Right, it's rare.

722
00:32:30,782 --> 00:32:34,352
Seolleongtang has little meat.
Galbitang is expensive.

723
00:32:34,419 --> 00:32:36,888
But gukbap that's cheap but filling

724
00:32:36,955 --> 00:32:39,691
is sundae gukbap,
which is comfort food for me.

725
00:32:39,757 --> 00:32:41,192
For less than 10,000 won.

726
00:32:41,793 --> 00:32:46,531
Sundae gukbap is the one and only
gukbap with that much meat.

727
00:32:46,597 --> 00:32:49,867
In our culture, we can ask
for more broth, which is filling.

728
00:32:49,934 --> 00:32:52,570
I eat sundae gukbap when I'm most hungry.

729
00:32:52,637 --> 00:32:56,607
It's very satisfying,
and your belly and your heart feel full.

730
00:32:56,674 --> 00:32:58,977
I think that's what gukbap is.

731
00:32:59,310 --> 00:33:04,716
A GENEROUS BOWL OF WARMTH
SUNDAE GUKBAP

732
00:33:07,852 --> 00:33:11,456
SEOUL

733
00:33:11,522 --> 00:33:13,324
SEONGBUK-GU, SEOUL

734
00:33:13,391 --> 00:33:16,427
I ate gamjatang in university.
It was expensive for me.

735
00:33:16,494 --> 00:33:17,762
It was a party food.

736
00:33:17,829 --> 00:33:20,898
If the upperclassmen were
at a gamjatang place,

737
00:33:20,965 --> 00:33:22,500
the lowerclassmen wanted to go.

738
00:33:22,567 --> 00:33:25,236
Each person would be holding a bone
and be sucking on it.

739
00:33:25,303 --> 00:33:27,205
It was a lot to eat.

740
00:33:27,271 --> 00:33:29,807
That's why it's usually found
next to universities.

741
00:33:31,309 --> 00:33:33,144
I feel younger on Daehak-ro.

742
00:33:33,211 --> 00:33:35,246
The atmosphere helps.

743
00:33:35,313 --> 00:33:37,048
There's youth in the air.

744
00:33:37,749 --> 00:33:39,083
The energy is different.

745
00:33:39,150 --> 00:33:40,084
I think it's here.

746
00:33:40,151 --> 00:33:40,985
Is it here?

747
00:33:41,052 --> 00:33:43,287
It's been a while seeing gamjaguk

748
00:33:43,354 --> 00:33:45,056
instead of gamjatang.

749
00:33:45,123 --> 00:33:47,658
Wow, it's been running since 1958.

750
00:33:48,126 --> 00:33:50,762
Wow, it really is an old store.

751
00:33:50,828 --> 00:33:52,630
-Hello.
-Hello.

752
00:33:54,565 --> 00:33:56,434
Considering it's a gamjaguk house,

753
00:33:56,501 --> 00:33:57,935
it's very tidy.

754
00:34:00,171 --> 00:34:01,005
Hello.

755
00:34:01,072 --> 00:34:01,939
-Hello.
-Hello.

756
00:34:02,006 --> 00:34:03,608
-Hi.
-You're the owner?

757
00:34:03,674 --> 00:34:05,176
Yes, third generation.

758
00:34:05,243 --> 00:34:07,145
Wow, the third generation.

759
00:34:07,211 --> 00:34:08,713
You're more handsome in person.

760
00:34:09,380 --> 00:34:10,248
Thank you.

761
00:34:10,314 --> 00:34:11,315
So this year marks--

762
00:34:11,382 --> 00:34:12,417
The 65th year.

763
00:34:12,483 --> 00:34:14,085
-The 65th year.
-Yes.

764
00:34:14,152 --> 00:34:15,586
That's amazing.

765
00:34:16,254 --> 00:34:17,989
When my grandparents owned this,

766
00:34:18,056 --> 00:34:20,091
they cooked it in large pots

767
00:34:20,158 --> 00:34:23,895
